{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17659583","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17659583"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T23:11:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T23:11:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20874"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20874","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20874"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.06,0.58,0.07,0.22]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13749"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96551"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13749","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13749"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20874"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79185"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11727"},{"type":"tags","id":"12697"},{"type":"tags","id":"12698"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"33099"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33112"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96551"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA hospital laboratory receives various specimens for testing throughout the day. The laboratory staff document errors that occur during the total testing process, which includes pre-analytical, analytical, and post-analytical phases.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents a pre-analytical error in laboratory testing?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transcription error in results","Delayed notification of critical results","Test request unintelligible","Incorrect reference range applied","Instrument calibration failure"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Etest request unintelligible\u003C/strong\u003E. This is a pre-analytical error that occurs before the specimen reaches the laboratory for analysis. When test requests are illegible, incomplete, or unclear, laboratory staff cannot determine which tests to perform, potentially leading to delays, incorrect testing, or rejection of the specimen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent errors from other phases of testing:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInstrument calibration failure\u003C/strong\u003E is an analytical error that occurs during the actual testing process in the laboratory.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncorrect reference range applied\u003C/strong\u003E is a post-analytical error that occurs when interpreting results after testing is complete.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETranscription error in results\u003C/strong\u003E is a post-analytical error that occurs when transferring or recording test results.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelayed notification of critical results\u003C/strong\u003E is a post-analytical error related to the communication of results after testing.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPre-analytical errors account for approximately 60-70% of all errors in laboratory testing and include problems with test ordering, patient identification, specimen collection, specimen labeling, specimen transport, and specimen processing. Addressing these errors is crucial for improving laboratory quality and patient safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pre-analytical errors occur before laboratory analysis and include issues with test ordering, patient preparation, specimen collection, and transport.","Unintelligible test requests are a common pre-analytical error that can lead to delayed or incorrect testing.","Pre-analytical errors account for approximately 60-70% of all errors in the total testing process."],"references":["Mrazek C, Lippi G, Keppel MH, Felder TK, Oberkofler H, Haschke-Becher E, Cadamuro J. Errors within the total laboratory testing process, from test selection to medical decision-making - A review of causes, consequences, surveillance and solutions. Biochem Med (Zagreb). 2020 Jun 15;30(2):020502. doi: 10.11613/BM.2020.020502. PMID: 32550813; PMCID: PMC7271754. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7271754/#sec21"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79185"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20874"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79185","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79185"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-02T08:40:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-02T11:31:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13749"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96551"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11260"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Professionalism","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2025-01-14T04:23:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T04:23:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"14"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11727","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tag